.TH "WEBTRANSPORTSENDSTREAM.SENDORDER" "3JS" "February 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebTransportSendStream.sendOrder \- WebTransportSendStream: sendOrder
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]sendOrder\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]WebTransportSendStream\f[R] interface indicates the send priority
of this stream relative to other streams for which the value has been
set.
.PP
Queued bytes are sent first for streams that have a higher value.
If not set, the send order depends on the implementation.
.SH VALUE
A number indicating the relative priority of this stream when sending
bytes.
.SH EXAMPLES
The example below shows how you can set the initial \f[CR]sendOrder\f[R]
when calling \f[CR]WebTransport.createUnidirectionalStream()\f[R] to
create the send stream, read the value from the stream, and then change
the order.
After changing the order the priority of this stream would increase,
becoming higher than any stream with a priority of less than
\(lq596996858\(rq.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] writeData() {
  \f[B]const\f[R] stream = \f[B]await\f[R] transport.createUnidirectionalStream({
    sendOrder: \(dq400\(dq, \f[I]// Set initial stream order\f[R]
  });

  console.log(\(gaStream order: ${stream.sendOrder}\(ga); \f[I]// Stream order: 400\f[R]

  \f[I]// write data ...\f[R]

  \f[I]// Change the stream order\f[R]
  stream.sendOrder = 596996858;
  console.log(\(gaStream order: ${stream.sendOrder}\(ga); \f[I]// Stream order: 596996858\f[R]

  \f[I]// write more data ...\f[R]
}
.EE
